    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-06-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-06-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="757"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d757">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2075.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-06-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 20, 1911</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 387]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 621 of the
                    3d instant and approves your course in addressing the note, a copy of which you
                    inclose, to the Mexican foreign office, in which you intimate to the Mexican
                    Government that, unless adequate protection should be afforded, that Government
                    would be held liable for all loss of life and damage to property of Americans in
                    the event of a mob outbreak in Mexico City.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.],</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
